        <body>
            <p>(Hebrew)</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>, <date>Sunday, 2 day<lb/>of Rosh
                    Hodesh, Tammuz (July) 1848</date>.</p>
            <p>Toâ€”<addressee>Yitzchok Isaac</addressee>, surnamed <addressee>Rev.
                Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p>Again I come to beg of you a favor in the<lb/> matter of the great and learned
                    <persName>Rabbi Moses<lb/> Katzenellenbogen</persName>. We turn to you with
                letters to be<lb/> translated from Hebrew into English. These are a<lb/> few words
                about our holy religion. Our pur-<lb/>pose is that he should be given permission to
                arrange<lb/> divorces. This is a matter of great importance for<lb/> him. That is
                why I am forced to ask you once more<lb/> to please let me know by return mail at
                the<lb/> address written below, whether the letters reached<lb/> you. With greetings
                of peace to you and all your<lb/> dear ones,<lb/> Expectantly yours,</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Isaac Finkelstein</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <sic>Adress</sic>
                <lb/>
                <persName>Rev. Moses Bougin</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
